# backend/.dockerignore — 1.9.0 W1 (QA-DEBT hygiene).
# The Dockerfile COPYies explicit paths (app/, alembic/, tests/, scripts/), so this
# file mostly shrinks the build-context upload: without it the local .venv (~hundreds
# of MB) and tool caches are shipped to the daemon on every build.
# NOTE: tests/ is still copied into the DEFAULT stage on purpose (CI runs them
# in-container). 1.9.1 W4 (SEC-DEPS-1) added a SEPARATE "production" stage (additional
# `--target production` build) that never copies tests/ or installs dev deps — see the
# Dockerfile header comment. The default stage (and every existing build path) is
# unchanged.

.venv/
venv/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
*.egg-info/
.env
*.log

# iCloud sync duplicates (QA-DEBT-1)
* [0-9]
* [0-9].*
